Exam

*********************************************
Sending &array[0]

Wrong:		ft_swap (array[0], array[1])
Correct		ft_swap (&array[0], &array[1]) 

When we want to send array indexes 

Ft-swap (&array[0], &array[1])

When we want to receive them 

void ft_swap(int *a, int *b) {}

When we want to use them 

 void ft_swap(int *a, int *b) 
{
	int (whatever it is)	tmp;
	
	tmp = *a;
	*a = *b;
	*b = tmp;
}
*********************************************
With pointers you do not need to return
